    <subsubsection>
      <title><xref ref="exer_contradiction_coprime"></xref> Select Answers and Hints</title>
      <p>
        Hint: If <m>p \mid a</m> and <m>p \mid b</m>,
        then <m>p</m> is a positive common divisor of <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> that is greater than one.
        What does that tell you about <m>\fn{gcd}(a,b)</m>?
      </p>
    </subsubsection>
